Boil a full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a #large saucepan{} with @salt{0.25%tsp} on high heat. Add the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{260%g} and sliced pepper. Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{}.

Stir-fry until the chicken is browned all over, ~{5-6%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Add the garlic, @Mexican Style Spice Mix{1}(add less if you'd prefer things milder) and @Tomato Puree{30%g} to the chicken. Stir-fry for ~{30%secs}.

Stir in the @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g}, @Sugar{1} and @Water{150%ml} for the sauce. Season with salt and pepper.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat.

Simmer, stirring occasionally, until the sauce has thickened and the chicken is cooked, ~{8-10%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, cut the @Medium Tomato{1} into 1cm pieces.

Roughly chop the @Coriander{1}(roughly chopped)(stalks and all).

Pop the tomatoes and half the coriander into a #bowl{} with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}. Season with salt and pepper, then set your salsa aside.

When everything's ready, fluff the rice up with a #fork{}. Stir through the remaining coriander, then share between your bowls.

Taste the chicken fajita mix, season with more salt and pepper if needed, then spoon it over the rice.

Top with the salsa and a big dollop of @Soured Cream{75%g}.

Enjoy!